    <title>Opioid QuOTA Act</title>
    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2018-03-09T22:17:20Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Opioid Quota Openness, Transparency, and Awareness Act of 2017 or the Opioid QuOTA Act</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Controlled Substances Act to require the Drug Enforcement Administration (DEA) to publish on its website certain information with respect to a registered manufacturer&rsquo;s opioid procurement quota.</p> <p>It defines the term &quot;opioid procurement quota&quot; as a quota established by the DEA for the quantity of opioid analgesics that a registered manufacturer may procure.</p>]]></text>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
          <actionDate>2017-09-28</actionDate>
          <updateDate>2017-09-28T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        </item>
